etymologies: mid 19th century; earliest use found in The Penny Cyclopaedia. From scientific Latin Mytilacea (H. M. D. de Blainville Man. de malacologie et conchyliologie 531; from Mytilus + -acea, after French Mytilacés (Cuvier, 1817), Mytilacées (Lamarck, 1819)) + -an

definitions: A bivalve of the group Mytilacea (now a superfamily), which comprises marine mussels.
Of, belonging to, or characteristic of the group Mytilacea of marine mussels.
